(113, 1, 'ckeditor', 'Описание', 'Блок 4', 6, 4, 0, '<p>Since 1996, the Central Testing Laboratory has advanced its objective to demonstrate that it operates in a management system, that it has high technical competence and can generate technically valid results. The objective was met and the laboratory obtained the initial accreditation, according to the requirements of the international standard EN ISO/IEC 17025, on December 25, 1996.&nbsp;<br><br>Until now, the Central Testing Laboratory maintains and continuously improves a management system in accordance with the requirements of the SM EN ISO/IEC standard 17025:2018 and applies in its own activity the specific documents developed by EA, ILAC, national and international standards, MOLDAC rules and procedures, including the requirements of the Integrated System of Quality and Food Safety Management (ISO 9001:2015 and ISO 22000:2005).<br>The main objectives of the LCÎ quality policy are:</p><ul><li>Maintaining trust, by demonstrating the laboratory\'s ability to perform tests at national and international level, according to legal requirements and applicable regulatory requirements;</li><li>Ensuring a high level of staff qualification, while maintaining good professional practice, for the qualitative realization of testing services under conditions of confidentiality and impartiality towards clients.</li><li>Fulfilling clients\' requests in the activity of regulated tests and responding promptly to their requests.</li></ul><p>Communicating the customer\'s opinion is very important for the laboratory, as it provides the opportunity to identify potential risks and take improvement measures. However, if they have complaints, regarding the functioning of the LCÎ or regarding the test reports issued, the laboratory treats them with all the attention to resolve them. The PSM 7.9 “Complaints” procedure is available, upon request, to any interested party.<br><br>Finally, it is important to mention that, for the achieved performances, the Management at the highest level of SA \"Bucuria\" undertook and maintains a series of actions:</p><ul><li>ensures the impartiality, independence and integrity of the laboratory staff, including the exclusion of any external influence on the results of the laboratory\'s activity;</li><li>ensures a high level of technical training of the personnel and the technical equipment necessary to perform the specific tests, taking into account the requirements of the test methods;</li><li>allocates the necessary resources for the good functioning of the testing laboratory and the continuous improvement of the management system.</li></ul>'),
